        <h2>Common Issues with Summit Commercial Ice Machines</h2>
        <p>Regular maintenance and timely repairs are essential for keeping Summit ice machines running smoothly. Some of the most common problems include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ice machine not making ice</strong> – Can be caused by a clogged water filter, faulty water inlet valve, or compressor failure.</li>
            <li><strong>Slow ice production</strong> – Often due to dirty condenser coils, inadequate water flow, or a malfunctioning thermostat.</li>
            <li><strong>Leaking water</strong> – Usually a result of a damaged pump, improper drainage, or a cracked water line.</li>
            <li><strong>Misshapen or small ice cubes</strong> – Typically caused by a malfunctioning water inlet valve or incorrect water flow settings.</li>
            <li><strong>Unusual noise during operation</strong> – May indicate worn-out fan motors, failing bearings, or loose internal components.</li>
        </ul>
        
